{"SYNE":[{"def":"Afterwards; since; ago.","pos":""},{"def":"Late, -- as opposed to soon.","pos":""}],"SYNECDOCHICAL":[{"def":"Expressed by synecdoche; implying a synecdoche.","pos":""}],"SYNECHIA":[{"def":"A disease of the eye, in which the iris adheres to the cornea or to the capsule of the crystalline lens.","pos":""}],"SYNECPHONESIS":[{"def":"A contraction of two syllables into one; synizesis.","pos":""}],"SYNEDRAL":[{"def":"Growing on the angles of a stem, as the leaves in some species of Selaginella.","pos":""}],"SYNENTOGNATHI":[{"def":"An order of fishes, resembling the Physoclisti, without spines in the dorsal, anal, and ventral fins.","pos":""}],"SYNEPY":[{"def":"The interjunction, or joining, of words in uttering the clauses of sentences.","pos":""}],"SYNERESIS":[{"def":"Same as Synæresis.","pos":""}],"SYNERGETIC":[{"def":"Working together; coöperating; as, synergetic muscles.","pos":""}],"SYNERGISM":[{"def":"The doctrine or theory, attributed to Melanchthon, that in the regeneration of a human soul there is a coöperation, or joint agency, on the part both of God and of man.","pos":""}],"SYNERGIST":[{"def":"A remedy which has an action similar to that of another remedy, and hence increases the efficiency of that remedy when combined with it.","pos":""}],"SYNERGISTIC":[{"def":"Of or pertaining to synergism.","pos":""},{"def":"Coöperating; synergetic.","pos":""}],"SYNERGY":[{"def":"Combined action; especially (Med.","pos":""},{"def":"the combined healty action of every organ of a particular system; as, the digestive synergy.","pos":""}],"SYNESIS":[{"def":"A construction in which adherence to some element in the sense causes a departure from strict syntax, as in \"Philip went down to Samaria and preached Christ unto them.","pos":""}]}